Yaws, re-emergence - Papua New Guinea 980911225040
Date: Sun, 13 Sep 1998 20:35:14 -0500
From: Robin Hide <rhide@coombs.anu.edu.au>
Via: Leslie Marshall <leslie-marshall@uiowa.edu>

The "eradication" [of yaws in PNG has long been known not to have been
longterm; for the last 12 years or so there have been regular accounts from
both PNG and Solomons of
the "reemergence"; see for instance:
Duncan, L. E. and W. Alto (1987). "An investigation of yaws on the
Trobriand Islands, 1985." Papua New Guinea Medical Journal 30(1): 57-61.
Eason, R. J. and T. Tasman-Jones (1985). "Resurgent yaws and other skin
diseases in the Western Province of the Solomon Islands." Papua New Guinea
Medical Journal 28(4): 247-50.
Garner, P. A., E. N. Talwat, et al. (1986). "Yaws reappears." Papua New
Guinea Medical Journal 29(3): 247-52.
Hudson, B. J., J. L. Backhouse, et al. (1990). "Management of yaws in Papua
New Guinea." Papua New Guinea Medical Journal 33(1): 59-65.
